      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "SEATTLE, Dot. 30.--Washing-\nton suffragists are not going to\nadopt the militant tactics of Eng\nlish suffragettes, according to\nstatement by Mrs. Emma Smith\nDevoe, president of the Washing.\nton Equal Suffrage association\ndiscussing the action Of Iowa suf.\nfragists this week. She said:\n\n\n1--WE don't fight and do not have\nto. We have obtained everything\nwe wanted. The last legislature\ntreated us very courteously. We\nare working now, not fighting, for\nwe are carrying on campaign for\nthe election of November g.. 1910\nwhen our cause will be placed be-\nfore the voters of the state\""
    }
  ]
